				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The reason is due to internal latching. The low three bits of the horizontal offset are special and used for internal tile rendering/fetching. You can think of them as actually separate registers internally. Or not, I'm not your father :P<br /><br />This matters. Try running Theme Park, it'll screw up if you don't do the horizontal scroll latching correctly. Stuff like this, it's best to just grit your teeth and implement it as we've described it :/<br /><br />It's screwy, yes, but it's not nearly as bad as the NES' loopy_t/v stuff.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

